German Union Demands 6.5 Percent Pay Raise for Retail Staff

-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 
2011-03-17T16:09:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/german-union-demands-6-5-percent-pay-raise-for-retail-staff.html
  Germany ’s Ver.di services union
demanded a 6.5 percent wage increase, or a minimum raise of 130
euros, for retail workers in North-Rhine Westphalia, the
country’s most populous state.  The union also called for temporary workers in the state’s
retail industry to be paid the same as permanent workers, the
local branch of  Ver.di in North-Rhine Westphalia  said in a
statement e-mailed from Dusseldorf today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
